Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.08,0:00:05.81,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, at 10:00 AM JST,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.81,0:00:09.75,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,the Midsummer's Knights will return with \Nthe Engine series to Tanegashima,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.75,0:00:13.53,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,aboard the container capsule Flügel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.56,0:00:16.23,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,We only have until tomorrow, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.23,0:00:18.85,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,We've gotta get close to him \Nwhile we have the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:19.74,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.26,0:00:21.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.40,0:00:25.98,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hana, Pitz is doing much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.34,0:00:28.27,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Pitz!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.01,0:00:31.84,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akari, thanks for taking care of Pitz.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:34.29,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.29,0:00:37.72,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We're friends. Right, Pitz?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.92,0:00:42.14,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.78,0:00:46.07,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Preparations for the operation \Nare in their final stages.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.68,0:00:50.27,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Sending Hana Mutou back to Earth will be risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.27,0:00:52.04,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'm aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.75,0:00:54.95,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I left Daichi and Teppei there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.70,0:00:57.95,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you two to protect Hana.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.38,0:00:59.22,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.19,0:01:01.16,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.58,0:01:02.51,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.35,0:01:06.50,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm with these two, I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.39,0:01:14.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Move the plan B tests into \Nphase 2 by the time they return.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.64,0:01:17.78,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei Arashi's test was completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.78,0:01:19.72,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is Daichi Manatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.98,0:01:22.38,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.11,0:02:58.42,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine Impacter has reached \Nthe test area in Sigma sector.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.42,0:02:59.99,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Standby confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.19,0:03:03.80,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Orgone spectrometer, calorimeter,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.80,0:03:06.30,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,and other observation instruments \Nare transmitting clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.75,0:03:07.95,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Ready any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.67,0:03:11.48,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, we're ready here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.32,0:03:12.79,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.08,0:03:16.94,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.61,0:03:31.47,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,How does it look?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.47,0:03:34.31,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Maximum output is 1.7 gigajoules.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.93,0:03:37.02,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei-kun's output is higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.74,0:03:40.53,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Though it's still only 1.8 gigajoules.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.03,0:03:47.53,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,A minimum of 2.0 gigajoules is required \Nto fire the boosted plasmagnum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.88,0:03:51.04,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,In actual combat, Teppei-kun \Nhas shown an output of 2.2,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:54.92,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,and the captain 2.1 gigajoules.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:58.88,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that the level hasn't stabilized \Nis our greatest concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.68,0:04:03.34,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But we're entrusting them with everything, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.64,0:04:14.65,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Onslaught Through \Nthe Wilderness
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.64,0:04:33.38,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is it true you don't have a girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.38,0:04:34.34,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.34,0:04:35.85,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a girl you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.67,0:04:37.64,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.68,0:04:43.42,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Does he, I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:45.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.88,0:04:49.72,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.75,0:04:55.19,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.88,0:04:58.65,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need something, Governor?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.75,0:05:17.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.56,0:05:23.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know anything about Kivotos?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.69,0:05:26.88,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a spaceship?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.22,0:05:32.85,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I called you here to ask a personal question.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.21,0:05:38.75,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I'm interested in you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.19,0:05:40.11,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.76,0:05:43.19,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm not a normal person?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.19,0:05:45.29,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,No, not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.90,0:05:49.66,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Because Akari called you her friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.74,0:05:55.45,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Since she was little, she's never \Nbeen able to make friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.45,0:05:57.86,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Or perhaps she simply refused to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:06:03.17,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,You're the first person I've ever \Nheard her call a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.02,0:06:06.38,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akari is my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.69,0:06:10.85,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.85,0:06:12.96,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.98,0:06:14.81,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.74,0:06:18.38,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm her mother... I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.38,0:06:24.82,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, I think Akari doesn't need me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.41,0:06:26.96,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Did Akari say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.51,0:06:32.81,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,It only makes sense that she'd feel that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.47,0:06:36.14,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that I left her alone for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.14,0:06:39.12,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I've only been her mother when \Nit was convenient for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.29,0:06:43.34,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akari isn't the kind of girl to think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.88,0:06:47.04,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a family...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.87,0:06:51.06,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But I have Akari, Teppei, and Daichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.79,0:06:53.34,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.58,0:06:56.18,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But when I see you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.72,0:07:00.39,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I think having a family must be nice, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.12,0:07:03.27,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.06,0:07:09.36,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Because whenever you talk about \NAkari, you look so kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.48,0:07:21.41,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.52,0:07:26.43,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Can I stay like this a little longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.39,0:07:32.18,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,This is what a mom smells like, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.76,0:07:38.13,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.78,0:07:47.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kivotos will only be able to fulfill its true mission
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.51,0:07:50.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,after docking with another spaceship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.29,0:07:55.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This ship is humanity's last hope for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.94,0:08:00.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Professor Canis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.79,0:08:04.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I worked on the development of Kivotos.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.88,0:08:05.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.75,0:08:08.34,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi Manatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.34,0:08:12.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that name before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.51,0:08:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:19.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you're the captain of \Nthe Midsummer's Knights?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.13,0:08:25.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What an honor to meet a hero here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:27.77,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.50,0:08:30.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I won't have this chance again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.21,0:08:34.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Please shake my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.54,0:08:38.24,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Rechecking the return orbit to Tanegashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.84,0:08:42.83,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,All three ordinaries are mounted in the container.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.35,0:08:47.50,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei-kun, next time you come back \Nup here, let's go swimming again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.04,0:08:48.83,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.30,0:08:51.71,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You're popular, Teppei!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.13,0:08:55.68,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Hana, give Akari my regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.10,0:08:57.88,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.04,0:09:01.79,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You seem different, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:06.43,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.21,0:09:10.27,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,A scientist I met here shook my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.93,0:09:12.23,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shook your hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.08,0:09:22.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the chosen hero's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.80,0:09:29.28,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,He said my hand was "the chosen hero's hand."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.38,0:09:33.37,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.75,0:09:39.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.13,0:09:42.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're no hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.83,0:09:48.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're only a child who happened to get a Livlaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:52.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're about to realize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.99,0:10:03.27,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Return program entering final sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.81,0:10:05.08,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shutting down main thruster.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.87,0:10:08.78,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Deceleration thrusters stopped two \Nseconds earlier than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.46,0:10:15.01,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Recalculated orbit shows no problems \Nwith atmospheric reentry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.74,0:10:19.47,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll land a good distance \Naway from the original point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.82,0:10:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.93,0:10:25.93,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The Flügel has entered the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.48,0:10:28.01,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Tracing estimated course...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.31,0:10:30.73,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I have their landing point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.37,0:10:32.70,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It's in Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:37.77,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They got us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.77,0:10:39.66,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,A spy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.66,0:10:42.64,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Hundreds of staff members are on the {\i1}Tenkaidou{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.64,0:10:45.12,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Some must be Ark Faction extremists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.74,0:10:47.83,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The return program was altered?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.26,0:10:51.54,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,If this is the Ark Faction's doing, \Nthey must be after Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.92,0:10:56.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Flügel has crash-landed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.42,0:11:00.47,Default,Point,0000,0000,0000,,Australia SE area 6!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.47,0:11:02.03,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The desert?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.03,0:11:03.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Can we contact the Flügel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.63,0:11:05.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is Tanegashima!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.00,0:11:06.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you copy, Flügel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.86,0:11:09.12,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This is Manatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.12,0:11:10.77,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We've crash-landed successfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:12.12,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,No one's hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:14.01,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We will now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.62,0:11:17.69,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Daichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.18,0:11:20.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We've lost communication with the Flügel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.46,0:11:22.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,An aurora storm is occurring!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.83,0:11:24.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Electromagnetic fluctuations are affecting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.69,0:11:27.66,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,That solar flare has reached Earth, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.67,0:11:32.99,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy's plans even accounted for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.50,0:11:38.63,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I lost contact with the base.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.07,0:11:42.43,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Close-range communications like this work fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.43,0:11:44.48,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They deliberately sent us here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.00,0:11:48.64,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Australian Central Command is nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.16,0:11:51.72,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We should assume this is all a trap by the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.46,0:11:56.43,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.43,0:11:57.57,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get home safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.58,0:12:03.42,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Livlaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.12,0:12:13.58,Default,Pu,0000,0000,0000,,By mastering the Livlaster's use,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.22,0:12:19.55,Default,Pu,0000,0000,0000,,it should ultimately be possible \Nto generate infinite energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.00,0:12:23.25,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, they haven't mastered it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:25.72,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Their output is limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.17,0:12:31.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,But the Princess's Livlaster used ecdysis mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.81,0:12:36.23,Default,Pu,0000,0000,0000,,There's a good chance it will \Nbecome even more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.23,0:12:40.82,Default,Mo,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't we Planetary Gears fire the Livlaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.23,0:12:43.48,Default,Pu,0000,0000,0000,,I can find no logical answer to that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:47.21,Default,Pu,0000,0000,0000,,But reports from Globe scientists say
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.21,0:12:54.00,Default,Pu,0000,0000,0000,,they believe the Livlasters are extradimensional \Nlife forms that take the form of guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.01,0:12:58.37,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,They just aren't compatible with us, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.75,0:13:04.33,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Kube got dumped by Hitomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.33,0:13:06.22,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Can you keep him under control?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.83,0:13:12.86,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I've received no information that Hitomi \NMakino has dumped Masaki Kube.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.74,0:13:17.42,Default,Mo,0000,0000,0000,,What "information" do you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.42,0:13:20.90,Default,Mo,0000,0000,0000,,He's gone after every girl in the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.13,0:13:32.54,Default,Mo,0000,0000,0000,,Hitomi won't be able to take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.54,0:13:37.26,Default,Mo,0000,0000,0000,,He's like a monkey in heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.69,0:13:39.66,Default,Pu,0000,0000,0000,,A monkey?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:44.96,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Pitz.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.96,0:13:48.65,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get Hana and the others back with my magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.50,0:13:51.43,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.15,0:13:54.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Is Hana in danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:57.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I brought them down as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.16,0:13:59.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Pluck the flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.70,0:14:01.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.47,0:14:10.91,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's winter in the Southern Hemisphere, \Nbut it isn't that cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.46,0:14:15.61,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, this is my \Nfirst time in another country.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.42,0:14:19.25,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But you're in space all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.87,0:14:22.56,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Is space another country?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.75,0:14:27.44,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Teppei...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.30,0:14:30.51,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What's that lunch you're eating?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.87,0:14:34.26,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The girls on the {\i1}Tenkaidou{\i0} made it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.67,0:14:36.29,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You're so popular, Teppei!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.96,0:14:38.42,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You really are...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.73,0:14:45.54,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing like me, a guy whose first overseas trip \Nonly happened because of a crash-land.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.81,0:14:49.27,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Have you not traveled a lot, Daichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.42,0:14:54.50,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the most I've done is go to Tanegashima \Nwith my dad when I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:57.91,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,What were your mom and dad like, Daichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:15:01.27,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I never told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.27,0:15:04.22,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,My dad was a Globe space pilot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.66,0:15:10.62,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I think he died fighting the first \NKiltgang to attack Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.14,0:15:15.60,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Parents are kind of mysterious, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.74,0:15:20.93,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,What about your mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.00,0:15:25.65,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,My mom died of an illness when I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.36,0:15:29.45,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,So my uncle raised me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.02,0:15:33.14,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You don't remember your mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.50,0:15:37.55,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really remember her...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.12,0:15:39.20,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.36,0:15:42.92,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,No reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.84,0:15:47.92,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.05,0:16:02.54,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.12,0:16:07.16,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's fair to assume they're with \Nthe guys who crashed us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.94,0:16:10.18,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.18,0:16:12.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A message from the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.10,0:16:14.40,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,"Disarm and surrender."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.40,0:16:15.51,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What should we respond?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.51,0:16:16.68,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,No need to respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.23,0:16:18.19,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.49,0:16:21.37,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.90,0:16:24.00,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Guess it'll be hard to escape them...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.11,0:16:26.99,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.17,0:16:31.09,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.26,0:16:38.26,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Teppei!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:39.94,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We shouldn't fight if we don't have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.94,0:16:42.14,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's a UCAV, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.83,0:16:44.07,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And one of Globe's.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.54,0:16:45.68,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The Ark Faction?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.55,0:16:47.89,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.89,0:16:48.73,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.33,0:16:51.15,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Even if someone were piloting it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:53.45,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'd shoot them for the team's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:58.03,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The time will come when you'll \Nbe forced to make that choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.73,0:16:59.82,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You know that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.28,0:17:02.47,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.47,0:17:06.05,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,These days, there aren't many manned weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.66,0:17:11.05,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.80,0:17:16.70,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the end, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.63,0:17:21.65,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If it's the Ark Faction, they'll keep \Ncoming until they get Hana
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.11,0:17:23.50,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,because she controls the {\i1}Blume{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.43,0:17:26.69,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Artillery fire from 3 o'clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.38,0:17:30.63,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. They're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.63,0:17:31.77,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Ahead of us, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.73,0:17:40.21,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We were ambushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.63,0:17:41.45,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.50,0:17:47.42,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They've sent the tank brigade.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.42,0:17:50.80,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And they have us so carefully surrounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.80,0:17:53.13,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,These are unmanned, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.01,0:17:55.06,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.38,0:18:09.27,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,They're only attacking the Earth and Nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.87,0:18:11.01,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.01,0:18:14.49,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That UCAV was to see which one Hana's piloting!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.83,0:18:16.96,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.96,0:18:20.09,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You and I will be killed here, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.09,0:18:21.28,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.95,0:18:25.91,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, above you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.84,0:18:36.51,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,People on Earth are scarier than these guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:40.18,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It makes you wonder whom we're \Nprotecting and why, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.60,0:18:52.27,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.78,0:19:00.86,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.25,0:19:01.95,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.09,0:19:15.49,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, the Nebula Engine is down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.49,0:19:16.51,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I can't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.12,0:19:18.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Take Hana and run!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.71,0:19:23.59,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,If they're here to capture me and won't \Nattack me, I can protect you both.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.59,0:19:25.85,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Getting out of here isn't our only mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.85,0:19:31.07,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't taking Hana back safely \Nto Tanegashima our mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.31,0:19:35.79,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Once the smoke clears, \Nthey'll attack us all at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.51,0:19:40.91,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Before that happens, leave me and go, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.87,0:19:52.58,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the chosen hero's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.98,0:19:58.38,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,He said my hand was "the chosen hero's hand."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.22,0:20:01.95,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.17,0:20:05.26,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't chosen by fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.81,0:20:08.57,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,You chose everything of your own free will,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.06,0:20:13.23,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,and you can grasp everything with that hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.68,0:20:15.30,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.68,0:20:28.87,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.25,0:20:39.38,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.05,0:20:42.59,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Can I grasp it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.84,0:20:46.05,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,No, I will grasp it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.68,0:21:09.87,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.88,0:21:24.86,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you leave me and run?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.64,0:21:29.41,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't you have done the same thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.03,0:21:31.89,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You're being naïve, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.86,0:21:36.48,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep that up, you'll lose \Nsomething really important someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.91,0:21:41.94,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But thank you for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.02,0:21:45.79,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That attack was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.22,0:21:48.01,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of output did you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.63,0:21:50.01,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Output?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.16,0:21:55.41,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,5.8 gigajoules?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.45,0:21:58.62,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,5.8 gigajoules?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.75,0:22:02.67,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.03,0:22:05.41,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei, is the Nebula okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.92,0:22:08.27,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like it will explode or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.42,0:22:11.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But it can't walk on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.42,0:22:14.10,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The two of us can carry the Nebula, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.75,0:22:18.06,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's go to Australia Central Command.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.06,0:22:21.37,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If we can get it that far, it'll probably be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.39,0:22:30.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Midsummer's Knights are \Nheading for Central Command.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.30,0:22:34.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to put the flower back in her vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.52,0:22:38.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you capture Hana Mutou.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.13,0:22:43.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of humanity's future.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.34,0:24:17.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We "borrow" a large transport plane \Nfrom Globe's Carpentaria base,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.93,0:24:21.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and set a course for Tanegashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.52,0:24:26.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But more new weapons \Nfrom Salty Dog attack us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.58,0:24:29.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This one's kind of bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.07,0:24:31.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Just then, right in front of us is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.54,0:24:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on episode 19 of {\i1}Captain Earth{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.49,0:24:36.58,Title2,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Smile Means Everything
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.85,0:24:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Smile Means Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.57,0:24:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine, expand!
